                    Certified Incident Handling Engineer (CIHE) Online Training Series
                    Course Notes


                    Course 01 - Introduction
Incident Handling can be defined as the preparation, detection, management and resolution of incidents or events that may occur
in the information system.                    
A security event is any event that occurs in the organization related to security.
Some common events include
  - Malicious Code Events
  - Network & Application Scans
  - Penetration Attempts
  - Espionage
  - Inappropriate use of assets
  

